        "subject": "LU-10482 tests: renumber sanity/56ea to avoid conflict",
        "message": "LU-10482 tests: renumber sanity/56ea to avoid conflict\n\nThere are two sanity test_56ca() tests, which exposed issues with\nthe naming schema in this set of subtests - that some test_56XX\nsubtests are in the \"abc\" sequence of tests, and others are in\nthe \"post-xyz\" sequence of tests and using \"aa, ab, ca, ...\".\n\nRename test_56ea*() and test_56Ea*() tests to avoid future collisions.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nChange-Id: I9f08e48c5b735498afa53b1a36202a9ce83ebbe5\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/65276\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Jian Yu <yujian@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Akash B <akash-b@hpe.com>\n"
      },
